{{Han compound|屰|月|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s|t2=moon}}

===Etymology===
From {{och-l|逆||to meet, to go against, reverse}} plus s-prefix. {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} interprets it as literally "turn again toward to meet"; while {{zh-ref|Baxter & Sagart (2014)}} interprets it as "when the moon changes from waning to waxing", with s- being a circumstantial prefix for place, time, & instrument.

